By Amen Gajira Minna – An 18-year-old labourer Joseph Thaddius, was on Monday docked in a Chief Magistrates’ Court in Minna, for allegedly attempting to steal bags of cement. Thaddius is facing a two-count charge of criminal trespass and attempted stealing. The Police Prosecutor, Insp. Aliyu Yakubu, told the court that one Zaradeen Adamu of Dutsten Kura, Minna, reported the matter at the GRA Police Station on June 17. According to Yakubu, the defendant trespassed into the place where the complainant sells cement and attempted to steal some bags of cement, but was caught and handed over to the police. He said the offences contravened sections 348 and 95 of the Penal Code. Thaddius, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Magistrate Mariam Kings, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N100, 000 and a surety in like sum. Kings adjourned the matter until June 27 for further mention. (NAN)